Cell.Text: [S] Approach Dragonborn. I have been waiting for you. How long has it been? My sense of time has grown meaningless in this place. | Can you hear them? Those who were, and those who are yet to be...they are all suffering. | This is the doing of our mother, Kyne, or so states the annals of The Chronicler.

[S] I am Arcadia Stormrunner. Though I possess a name, I do not know who I am. I came into being...laying gaze upon this Wall, my ears filled with its endless voices. | I cannot leave, for my existence is tied to it...fading if I stray too far, finding myself back here as always. | My identity is now the purpose imbued upon me. | I am to guide you, Dragonborn, that is my duty. You and I are to embark on a journey together. I have been granted with the knowledge to accomplish this task, and nothing more.

As the Dragonborn, it is your destiny to lead the Blades. | I sensed your presence upon your touching of the ring. Your visions were that of the Guardian's as he awakened due to his proximity to the power of the Wall.
As the Dragonborn, it is your destiny to lead the Blades. | I sensed your presence upon Aldiun's return, hearing the suffering via the power of the Wall.

[S] It is a sacred role held amongst the Blades. We must always have our records kept, the flame of knowledge must stay lit. | When it is time for them to meet their Kiss at the End, the mantle is passed onto a new brother or sister. | The previous Chronicler lay to rest here, in the Bone-Glyph Repository. There is much you must learn before you are to hear his story Dragonborn, and you will only be told once you are ready.
What does Kyne have to do with this?

[S] In the Ancient era, men worshipped the dragons as gods. Over time, the bond to their masters grew into one of oppression. | A long and terrible war was fought. It was the World Eater, Alduin, along with his lieutenant, Paarthurnax, who lead the charge against the rebellion of man. | Dragons are free of the limitations from which they were created. Time, Morality and Mortality - such thoughts are meaningless to their kind. | Thus, it is said, they committed unspeakable, merciless atrocities towards their enemies... | It was at this time, Kyne passed judgment upon the dragons, taking the side of man, arming them with a weapon powerful enough to bring an end to the war.

[S] Kyne cast her breath upon the Throat of the World, bestowing men with the gift of the Thu'um - a chance to fight back, to defeat the dragons using the power of their own voice. | It was Kyne's intervention that turned Paarthurnax to the Way of the Voice, secluding himself at the Throat of the World, willingly committed to aiding men for the rest of time. | Have you ever considered how this could be, Dragonborn? Paarthurnax, a mighty dragon, Son of Akatosh, how could he, imbued with such great power be swayed in such a way? | For one to truly understand, they can only be shown. Hear my voice and heed its message Dragonborn, for you have much to learn before you are truly worthy of leading the Blades.

[S] I knew it was time to act. I awakened the sleeping dragon, knowing it would result in a series of events that would lead you to me. | The voices. I can hear them all. I can foresee it all...the suffering. | Think of me what you will. But...I can assure you Dragonborn...it was the lesser of evils, given the alternative paths that lay ahead. | When it comes to war, whether it's in gold, blood, or power...we all pay a price.
[S] You saw all that you needed to see, and nothing more. The visions we share are a journey into the past of those who have suffered. | I...I have seen him before...Valronis. Was it...in a dream?
I have met Valronis. He is hunting me.
